Comment.value: Selected, someone has told him the password.

String over his head once door has been opened but nobody has told him the password.

This character is the chef in the Seedy Tavern
He stands in the room with the door going down to the tavern basement.
If someone opens the door (with a key or with lockpicking) he begins displaying a string over his head asking for someone to explain why it is open, or he will call the guards. If spoken to, he will ask the player for a password.
If the door is bashed, he should just run for the guards.
If the player quits out of dialogue with him and the door is open and nobody has told him the password, he should run for the guards.
If the player quits out of dialogue with him and (the door is closed) OR (the door is open but he has been told the password) he does nothing

Display over head if door has been opened but nobody has told him the password
